    "To solve the probability-flow ODE, we examine two solvers: the standard Euler solver and the fourth-order Runge-Kutta (RK) method [53].",
    "The RK method is an extension of the Euler method, which considers multiple values of the integrated function within the integration interval.",
    "It emphasises the midpoint value rather than the edges of the integration step.",
    "Finally, we evaluate the DDIM solver [51].",
    "This is a deterministic solver specifically designed for diffusion generative models."
